import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
gl = df.groupby('ObservationDate')['Confirmed'].sum().reset_index()

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.lineplot(x='ObservationDate', y='Confirmed', data=gl, color='g')
plt.title('Global COVID-19 Confirmed Cases Over Time')
plt.show()

plt.bar(country_sorted['Country/Region'], country_sorted['Mortality Rate'], color='red')

# 17. What is the trend of new confirmed cases over time globally?
In [51]:
df['ObservationDate'] = pd.to_datetime(df['ObservationDate']) 
df_sorted = df.sort_values(by='ObservationDate').reset_index(drop=True)
df_sorted['New Cases'] = df_sorted['Confirmed'].diff().fillna(df_sorted['Confirmed'])
daily_new_cases = df_sorted.groupby('ObservationDate')['New Cases'].sum().reset_index()

print(daily_new_cases)
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.lineplot(data=daily_new_cases, x='ObservationDate', y='New Cases', color='red')
plt.title('Trend of New Confirmed Cases Over Time Globally')

plt.show()

# 20.What is the trend of active cases over time globally?
In [55]:
df['ObservationDate'] = pd.to_datetime(df['ObservationDate'])  
df_sorted = df.sort_values(by='ObservationDate').reset_index(drop=True)
df_sorted['Active Cases'] = df_sorted['Confirmed'] - df_sorted['Recovered'] - df_sorted['Deaths']
daily_active_cases = df_sorted.groupby('ObservationDate')['Active Cases'].sum().reset_index()

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.lineplot(x='ObservationDate', y='Active Cases', data=daily_active_cases, color='red')
plt.show()
